definition.value: Liposaccharide natural compounds consisting of a trisaccharide repeating unit (two heptose units and octulosonic acid) with oligosaccharide side chains and 3-hydroxytetradecanoic acid units (they are a major constituent of the cell walls of Gram-negative bacteria).
A butynediol that is but-2-yne substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1 and 4.
A dibenzazecine alkaloid isolated from Fumaria vaillantii.
